.TH VIDEOS "1" "December 2025" "videos 202208180315-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
videos \- Play videos from the terminal
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B videos
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] [\fI\,FILE\/\fR...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B videos
is a script for playing video files from the terminal. It provides a simple interface for launching video playback using available media players.
.PP
The script supports various video formats and player backends.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-help
Display help message with usage information and available options
.TP
.BR \-\-config
Generate or regenerate user configuration file with default settings
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show script version information and exit
.TP
.BR \-\-options
Display all available command-line options
.TP
.BR \-\-debug
Enable debug mode with verbose output and command tracing (set -x)
.TP
.BR \-\-raw
Disable colorized output for plain text display
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B videos movie.mp4
Play a video file
.TP
.B videos ~/Videos/*.mkv
Play multiple video files
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.config/myscripts/videos/settings.conf
User configuration file for videos preferences
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
General error
.SH NOTES
.IP \(bu 2
Terminal application (reopens in terminal if needed)
.IP \(bu 2
Supports multiple video formats
.IP \(bu 2
Uses available media players
